In [1]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [2]:
%matplotlib inline
plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = [15, 10]  # Larger images
In [3]:
nasacolor = plt.imread("TarantulaNebula.jpeg")
In [4]:
plt.imshow(nasacolor);
In [5]:
nasa = np.sum(nasacolor, 2, np.float64)
m = np.amax(nasa)
nasa = nasa * 255 / m
In [6]:
plt.imshow(nasa, cmap="gray", vmin=0, vmax=255)
plt.title("Grayscale NASA photo");
In [7]:
u, s_vec, v = np.linalg.svd(nasa)
In [8]:
plt.semilogy(s_vec);
In [9]:
s = np.diag(s_vec)
nasa100 = u[:, :100] @ s[:100, :100] @ v[:100, :]
nasa50 = u[:, :50] @ s[:50, :50] @ v[:50, :]
nasa25 = u[:, :25] @ s[:25, :25] @ v[:25, :]
In [10]:
plt.imshow(nasa100, cmap="gray", vmin=0, vmax=255)
plt.title("NASA 100");
In [11]:
plt.imshow(nasa50, cmap="gray", vmin=0, vmax=255)
plt.title("NASA 50");
In [12]:
plt.imshow(nasa25, cmap="gray", vmin=0, vmax=255)
plt.title("NASA 25");
